==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Accipitres
<hw>Ac*cip"i*tres</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
hawks.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The order that includes rapacious
birds. They have a hooked bill, and sharp, strongly curved talons. There
are three families, represented by the vultures, the falcons or hawks,
and the owls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Accipitridae</ent>⟦br⟧
